<br>
Each class, to be balanced, should be able to solo while wearing store bought blue weapons/armor, optimal blue mobs with little difficulty using the skills of the class.  Non-optimal blues should provide a bit of difficulty, yellows should be a 50/50 gamble, etc.  I don't have the exact quote to put up here, but my point is that we have to look at what we DO have and see if with those skill combinations, if we can acheive solo PvE balance within the scope of our abilities.<br>
<br>
Whether or not an archer can or cannot solo X mob with relative ease has NOTHING AT ALL TO DO with whether assassins can or cannot.  Should we be able to meet the balance requirements?  God yes, and we're getting closer as time goes by.  But what any other class can or cannot do has no bearing at all with whether we are balanced.   The same measuring stick should be applied to them, individually, and each class needs to be individually balanced.  THEN realm balance looked at once the individual classes are in order.<br>
<br>
I said it in one of your other threads .. but the appearance of class envy is detrimental to your cause.  Even if that wasn't your original goal. <p>-- Huff McTuff, 40 Nightshade, Pendragon<br>
-- <i>Nightshade Team Lead</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukeybaud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>keybaud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 5:44:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1983.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Balance</span><hr size=1> Squink,<br>
<br>
Balance means equal. If a class has a 50% chance to defeat a yellow, he is not balanced until every class has the same chance, not a higher chance and not a lower chance, but the same.<br>
<br>
I challenge you to provide a list of classes who are not &quot;balanced&quot;. I want every class that has a higher chance than 50/50 as well as a lower chance.<br>
<br>
What Mythic have done is create a &quot;minimum&quot; requirement. This is not &quot;balance&quot;.<br>
<br>
Thank you.<br>
