Response:<br>
<br>
Archer's can't be like me (with my 40th Infilt). And I'll tell you why. Besides from the obvious reasons (skills, armour, etc), the style of play is totaly different, and THAT for me is a rush and something I will never give up. I'm talking mostly about RvR, because that's where I feel I am having the MOST fun (now) and will continue in the future.<br>
<br>
Archer. Sits high up on a hill, like a good sniper should. Waits for his moment while checking out the scenario. It's clear, he shoots, kills (or maims) and is far away enough to run. EASY!!!<br>
<br>
The andrenalin rush I get (and I don't think I'm a freak, because of it) when I'm right down smelling the Firebolg I'm hunting, and he's only a few steps away, and I move in for the kill. Man, my hands sometimes tremble at the keyboard, and I've done this 100 times. THAT to me, is what I love about my INfiltrator. The danger of getting caught, but even more the joy of success, when I slice him up, and make my getaway!<br>
<br>
--Someone mentioned how poisons are gimped? WHAT???! I'll tell you a little story-- I jumped an orange conning Lurkian the other day in Hibernia (I'm guessing 43ish), got him to half health, and he got two poisons away. The Evervating, and another. Mine got off too, and after a few more swings he decided to run. I try to follow, but can HARDLY MOVE. I check my stats quickly, and my STR is at 5!!!! Luckily, a mob jumped him, and my poison finished him off. NOW are you going to tell me poisons are gimped? Now, mind he had a skill (envenom) of 37 or 38, but I'm reaching for it, and I'm not going to whine in the meantime.<br>
<br>
--Lastly, someone mentioned how archers can ONE SHOT a blue caster, and we have to be &quot;bottom feeders&quot; (I believe was the term) to pray on the greens. I have ONE SHOT killed even yellow casters seldomly, and more then not I can ONE SHOT kill blue (anythings). I've engaged orange and even red mobs (when alone) and won. Just have to pick your fights.<br>
<br>
I love the excitment my infiltrator brings, and I love the way I play mine. Good luck to you all! <p><img src="http://fonsen.virtualave.net/images/Jaax55.jpg">
